## TTS (Text-to-Speech)

### Pre-generated audio (preferred)
Components should use `playTtsAudio()` which tries an MP3 file first, then falls back to browser TTS:
```tsx
import { getTtsAudioPath, playTtsAudio } from '@/lib/tts';

const audioPath = exerciseId
  ? getTtsAudioPath(exerciseId, 'words', cardId)
  : '';
playTtsAudio(audioPath, fallbackText);
```

### Browser TTS fallback
For cases without pre-generated audio, use the shared utility:
```tsx
import { speakBulgarian, stopSpeaking } from '@/lib/tts';
speakBulgarian('Здравейте!');
stopSpeaking();
```

### Model strategy (see `tts-audio` rule for details)
- **Flash** (`gemini-2.5-flash-tts`) — single words, grammar table rows/notes
- **Pro** (`gemini-2.5-pro-tts`) — sentences, dialogues, reading texts, personal choice models

## State Persistence

Use `useExercisePersistence` to save/restore exercise state across page navigations:

```tsx
import { useExercisePersistence } from '@/hooks/useExercisePersistence';

export function MyExercise({ exerciseId }: { exerciseId?: string }) {
  const { savedState, saveState } = useExercisePersistence(exerciseId);
  const s = savedState as any;

  const [answers, setAnswers] = useState(() => s?.answers ?? {});

  useEffect(() => {
    saveState({ answers, isSubmitted });
  }, [answers, isSubmitted]);
}
```
